12// The algorithm below is a reimplementation of former \src\LU\Inverse_SSE.h using PacketMath.
13// inv(M) = M#/|M|, where inv(M), M# and |M| denote the inverse of M,
14// adjugate of M and determinant of M respectively. M# is computed block-wise
15// using specific formulae. For proof, see:
16// https://lxjk.github.io/2017/09/03/Fast-4x4-Matrix-Inverse-with-SSE-SIMD-Explained.html
17// Variable names are adopted from \src\LU\Inverse_SSE.h.
18//
19// The SSE code for the 4x4 float and double matrix inverse in former (deprecated) \src\LU\Inverse_SSE.h
20// comes from the following Intel's library:
21// http://software.intel.com/en-us/articles/optimized-matrix-library-for-use-with-the-intel-pentiumr-4-processors-sse2-instructions/
22//
23// Here is the respective copyright and license statement:
24//
25// Copyright (c) 2001 Intel Corporation.
26//
27// Permition is granted to use, copy, distribute and prepare derivative works
28// of this library for any purpose and without fee, provided, that the above
29// copyright notice and this statement appear in all copies.
30// Intel makes no representations about the suitability of this software for
31// any purpose, and specifically disclaims all warranties.
32// See LEGAL.TXT for all the legal information.
33//
34// TODO: Unify implementations of different data types (i.e. float and double).
35#ifndef EIGEN_INVERSE_SIZE_4_H
36#define EIGEN_INVERSE_SIZE_4_H
37
38namespace Eigen
39{
40namespace internal
41{
42template <typename MatrixType, typename ResultType>
43struct compute_inverse_size4<Architecture::Target, float, MatrixType, ResultType>
44{
45 enum
46 {
47 MatrixAlignment = traits<MatrixType>::Alignment,
48 ResultAlignment = traits<ResultType>::Alignment,
49 StorageOrdersMatch = (MatrixType::Flags & RowMajorBit) == (ResultType::Flags & RowMajorBit)
50 };
51 typedef typename conditional<(MatrixType::Flags & LinearAccessBit), MatrixType const &, typename MatrixType::PlainObject>::type ActualMatrixType;
52
53 static void run(const MatrixType &mat, ResultType &result)
54 {
55 ActualMatrixType matrix(mat);
56
57 const float* data = matrix.data();
58 const Index stride = matrix.innerStride();
59 Packet4f _L1 = ploadt<Packet4f,MatrixAlignment>(data);
60 Packet4f _L2 = ploadt<Packet4f,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*4);
61 Packet4f _L3 = ploadt<Packet4f,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*8);
62 Packet4f _L4 = ploadt<Packet4f,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*12);
63
64 // Four 2x2 sub-matrices of the input matrix
65 // input = [[A, B],
66 // [C, D]]
67 Packet4f A, B, C, D;
68
69 if (!StorageOrdersMatch)
70 {
71 A = vec4f_unpacklo(a: _L1, b: _L2);
72 B = vec4f_unpacklo(a: _L3, b: _L4);
73 C = vec4f_unpackhi(a: _L1, b: _L2);
74 D = vec4f_unpackhi(a: _L3, b: _L4);
75 }
76 else
77 {
78 A = vec4f_movelh(a: _L1, b: _L2);
79 B = vec4f_movehl(a: _L2, b: _L1);
80 C = vec4f_movelh(a: _L3, b: _L4);
81 D = vec4f_movehl(a: _L4, b: _L3);
82 }
83
84 Packet4f AB, DC;
85
86 // AB = A# * B, where A# denotes the adjugate of A, and * denotes matrix product.
87 AB = pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(A, A, 3, 3, 0, 0), b: B);
88 AB = psub(a: AB, b: pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(A, A, 1, 1, 2, 2), vec4f_swizzle2(B, B, 2, 3, 0, 1)));
89
90 // DC = D#*C
91 DC = pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(D, D, 3, 3, 0, 0), b: C);
92 DC = psub(a: DC, b: pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(D, D, 1, 1, 2, 2), vec4f_swizzle2(C, C, 2, 3, 0, 1)));
93
94 // determinants of the sub-matrices
95 Packet4f dA, dB, dC, dD;
96
97 dA = pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(A, A, 3, 3, 1, 1), b: A);
98 dA = psub(a: dA, b: vec4f_movehl(a: dA, b: dA));
99
100 dB = pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(B, B, 3, 3, 1, 1), b: B);
101 dB = psub(a: dB, b: vec4f_movehl(a: dB, b: dB));
102
103 dC = pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(C, C, 3, 3, 1, 1), b: C);
104 dC = psub(a: dC, b: vec4f_movehl(a: dC, b: dC));
105
106 dD = pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(D, D, 3, 3, 1, 1), b: D);
107 dD = psub(a: dD, b: vec4f_movehl(a: dD, b: dD));
108
109 Packet4f d, d1, d2;
110
111 d = pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(DC, DC, 0, 2, 1, 3), b: AB);
112 d = padd(a: d, b: vec4f_movehl(a: d, b: d));
113 d = padd(a: d, vec4f_swizzle2(d, d, 1, 0, 0, 0));
114 d1 = pmul(a: dA, b: dD);
115 d2 = pmul(a: dB, b: dC);
116
117 // determinant of the input matrix, det = |A||D| + |B||C| - trace(A#*B*D#*C)
118 Packet4f det = vec4f_duplane(psub(padd(d1, d2), d), 0);
119
120 // reciprocal of the determinant of the input matrix, rd = 1/det
121 Packet4f rd = pdiv(a: pset1<Packet4f>(from: 1.0f), b: det);
122
123 // Four sub-matrices of the inverse
124 Packet4f iA, iB, iC, iD;
125
126 // iD = D*|A| - C*A#*B
127 iD = pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(C, C, 0, 0, 2, 2), b: vec4f_movelh(a: AB, b: AB));
128 iD = padd(a: iD, b: pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(C, C, 1, 1, 3, 3), b: vec4f_movehl(a: AB, b: AB)));
129 iD = psub(a: pmul(a: D, vec4f_duplane(dA, 0)), b: iD);
130
131 // iA = A*|D| - B*D#*C
132 iA = pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(B, B, 0, 0, 2, 2), b: vec4f_movelh(a: DC, b: DC));
133 iA = padd(a: iA, b: pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(B, B, 1, 1, 3, 3), b: vec4f_movehl(a: DC, b: DC)));
134 iA = psub(a: pmul(a: A, vec4f_duplane(dD, 0)), b: iA);
135
136 // iB = C*|B| - D * (A#B)# = C*|B| - D*B#*A
137 iB = pmul(a: D, vec4f_swizzle2(AB, AB, 3, 0, 3, 0));
138 iB = psub(a: iB, b: pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(D, D, 1, 0, 3, 2), vec4f_swizzle2(AB, AB, 2, 1, 2, 1)));
139 iB = psub(a: pmul(a: C, vec4f_duplane(dB, 0)), b: iB);
140
141 // iC = B*|C| - A * (D#C)# = B*|C| - A*C#*D
142 iC = pmul(a: A, vec4f_swizzle2(DC, DC, 3, 0, 3, 0));
143 iC = psub(a: iC, b: pmul(vec4f_swizzle2(A, A, 1, 0, 3, 2), vec4f_swizzle2(DC, DC, 2, 1, 2, 1)));
144 iC = psub(a: pmul(a: B, vec4f_duplane(dC, 0)), b: iC);
145
146 const float sign_mask[4] = {0.0f, numext::bit_cast<float>(src: 0x80000000u), numext::bit_cast<float>(src: 0x80000000u), 0.0f};
147 const Packet4f p4f_sign_PNNP = ploadu<Packet4f>(from: sign_mask);
148 rd = pxor(a: rd, b: p4f_sign_PNNP);
149 iA = pmul(a: iA, b: rd);
150 iB = pmul(a: iB, b: rd);
151 iC = pmul(a: iC, b: rd);
152 iD = pmul(a: iD, b: rd);
153
154 Index res_stride = result.outerStride();
155 float *res = result.data();
156
157 pstoret<float, Packet4f, ResultAlignment>(res + 0, vec4f_swizzle2(iA, iB, 3, 1, 3, 1));
158 pstoret<float, Packet4f, ResultAlignment>(res + res_stride, vec4f_swizzle2(iA, iB, 2, 0, 2, 0));
159 pstoret<float, Packet4f, ResultAlignment>(res + 2 * res_stride, vec4f_swizzle2(iC, iD, 3, 1, 3, 1));
160 pstoret<float, Packet4f, ResultAlignment>(res + 3 * res_stride, vec4f_swizzle2(iC, iD, 2, 0, 2, 0));
161 }
162};
163
164#if !(defined EIGEN_VECTORIZE_NEON && !(EIGEN_ARCH_ARM64 && !EIGEN_APPLE_DOUBLE_NEON_BUG))
165// same algorithm as above, except that each operand is split into
166// halves for two registers to hold.
167template <typename MatrixType, typename ResultType>
168struct compute_inverse_size4<Architecture::Target, double, MatrixType, ResultType>
169{
170 enum
171 {
172 MatrixAlignment = traits<MatrixType>::Alignment,
173 ResultAlignment = traits<ResultType>::Alignment,
174 StorageOrdersMatch = (MatrixType::Flags & RowMajorBit) == (ResultType::Flags & RowMajorBit)
175 };
176 typedef typename conditional<(MatrixType::Flags & LinearAccessBit),
177 MatrixType const &,
178 typename MatrixType::PlainObject>::type
179 ActualMatrixType;
180
181 static void run(const MatrixType &mat, ResultType &result)
182 {
183 ActualMatrixType matrix(mat);
184
185 // Four 2x2 sub-matrices of the input matrix, each is further divided into upper and lower
186 // row e.g. A1, upper row of A, A2, lower row of A
187 // input = [[A, B], = [[[A1, [B1,
188 // [C, D]] A2], B2]],
189 // [[C1, [D1,
190 // C2], D2]]]
191
192 Packet2d A1, A2, B1, B2, C1, C2, D1, D2;
193
194 const double* data = matrix.data();
195 const Index stride = matrix.innerStride();
196 if (StorageOrdersMatch)
197 {
198 A1 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*0);
199 B1 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*2);
200 A2 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*4);
201 B2 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*6);
202 C1 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*8);
203 D1 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*10);
204 C2 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*12);
205 D2 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*14);
206 }
207 else
208 {
209 Packet2d temp;
210 A1 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*0);
211 C1 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*2);
212 A2 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*4);
213 C2 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*6);
214 temp = A1;
215 A1 = vec2d_unpacklo(a: A1, b: A2);
216 A2 = vec2d_unpackhi(a: temp, b: A2);
217
218 temp = C1;
219 C1 = vec2d_unpacklo(a: C1, b: C2);
220 C2 = vec2d_unpackhi(a: temp, b: C2);
221
222 B1 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*8);
223 D1 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*10);
224 B2 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*12);
225 D2 = ploadt<Packet2d,MatrixAlignment>(data + stride*14);
226
227 temp = B1;
228 B1 = vec2d_unpacklo(a: B1, b: B2);
229 B2 = vec2d_unpackhi(a: temp, b: B2);
230
231 temp = D1;
232 D1 = vec2d_unpacklo(a: D1, b: D2);
233 D2 = vec2d_unpackhi(a: temp, b: D2);
234 }
235
236 // determinants of the sub-matrices
237 Packet2d dA, dB, dC, dD;
238
239 dA = vec2d_swizzle2(A2, A2, 1);
240 dA = pmul(a: A1, b: dA);
241 dA = psub(a: dA, vec2d_duplane(dA, 1));
242
243 dB = vec2d_swizzle2(B2, B2, 1);
244 dB = pmul(a: B1, b: dB);
245 dB = psub(a: dB, vec2d_duplane(dB, 1));
246
247 dC = vec2d_swizzle2(C2, C2, 1);
248 dC = pmul(a: C1, b: dC);
249 dC = psub(a: dC, vec2d_duplane(dC, 1));
250
251 dD = vec2d_swizzle2(D2, D2, 1);
252 dD = pmul(a: D1, b: dD);
253 dD = psub(a: dD, vec2d_duplane(dD, 1));
254
255 Packet2d DC1, DC2, AB1, AB2;
256
257 // AB = A# * B, where A# denotes the adjugate of A, and * denotes matrix product.
258 AB1 = pmul(a: B1, vec2d_duplane(A2, 1));
259 AB2 = pmul(a: B2, vec2d_duplane(A1, 0));
260 AB1 = psub(a: AB1, b: pmul(a: B2, vec2d_duplane(A1, 1)));
261 AB2 = psub(a: AB2, b: pmul(a: B1, vec2d_duplane(A2, 0)));
262
263 // DC = D#*C
264 DC1 = pmul(a: C1, vec2d_duplane(D2, 1));
265 DC2 = pmul(a: C2, vec2d_duplane(D1, 0));
266 DC1 = psub(a: DC1, b: pmul(a: C2, vec2d_duplane(D1, 1)));
267 DC2 = psub(a: DC2, b: pmul(a: C1, vec2d_duplane(D2, 0)));
268
269 Packet2d d1, d2;
270
271 // determinant of the input matrix, det = |A||D| + |B||C| - trace(A#*B*D#*C)
272 Packet2d det;
273
274 // reciprocal of the determinant of the input matrix, rd = 1/det
275 Packet2d rd;
276
277 d1 = pmul(a: AB1, vec2d_swizzle2(DC1, DC2, 0));
278 d2 = pmul(a: AB2, vec2d_swizzle2(DC1, DC2, 3));
279 rd = padd(a: d1, b: d2);
280 rd = padd(a: rd, vec2d_duplane(rd, 1));
281
282 d1 = pmul(a: dA, b: dD);
283 d2 = pmul(a: dB, b: dC);
284
285 det = padd(a: d1, b: d2);
286 det = psub(a: det, b: rd);
287 det = vec2d_duplane(det, 0);
288 rd = pdiv(a: pset1<Packet2d>(from: 1.0), b: det);
289
290 // rows of four sub-matrices of the inverse
291 Packet2d iA1, iA2, iB1, iB2, iC1, iC2, iD1, iD2;
292
293 // iD = D*|A| - C*A#*B
294 iD1 = pmul(a: AB1, vec2d_duplane(C1, 0));
295 iD2 = pmul(a: AB1, vec2d_duplane(C2, 0));
296 iD1 = padd(a: iD1, b: pmul(a: AB2, vec2d_duplane(C1, 1)));
297 iD2 = padd(a: iD2, b: pmul(a: AB2, vec2d_duplane(C2, 1)));
298 dA = vec2d_duplane(dA, 0);
299 iD1 = psub(a: pmul(a: D1, b: dA), b: iD1);
300 iD2 = psub(a: pmul(a: D2, b: dA), b: iD2);
301
302 // iA = A*|D| - B*D#*C
303 iA1 = pmul(a: DC1, vec2d_duplane(B1, 0));
304 iA2 = pmul(a: DC1, vec2d_duplane(B2, 0));
305 iA1 = padd(a: iA1, b: pmul(a: DC2, vec2d_duplane(B1, 1)));
306 iA2 = padd(a: iA2, b: pmul(a: DC2, vec2d_duplane(B2, 1)));
307 dD = vec2d_duplane(dD, 0);
308 iA1 = psub(a: pmul(a: A1, b: dD), b: iA1);
309 iA2 = psub(a: pmul(a: A2, b: dD), b: iA2);
310
311 // iB = C*|B| - D * (A#B)# = C*|B| - D*B#*A
312 iB1 = pmul(a: D1, vec2d_swizzle2(AB2, AB1, 1));
313 iB2 = pmul(a: D2, vec2d_swizzle2(AB2, AB1, 1));
314 iB1 = psub(a: iB1, b: pmul(vec2d_swizzle2(D1, D1, 1), vec2d_swizzle2(AB2, AB1, 2)));
315 iB2 = psub(a: iB2, b: pmul(vec2d_swizzle2(D2, D2, 1), vec2d_swizzle2(AB2, AB1, 2)));
316 dB = vec2d_duplane(dB, 0);
317 iB1 = psub(a: pmul(a: C1, b: dB), b: iB1);
318 iB2 = psub(a: pmul(a: C2, b: dB), b: iB2);
319
320 // iC = B*|C| - A * (D#C)# = B*|C| - A*C#*D
321 iC1 = pmul(a: A1, vec2d_swizzle2(DC2, DC1, 1));
322 iC2 = pmul(a: A2, vec2d_swizzle2(DC2, DC1, 1));
323 iC1 = psub(a: iC1, b: pmul(vec2d_swizzle2(A1, A1, 1), vec2d_swizzle2(DC2, DC1, 2)));
324 iC2 = psub(a: iC2, b: pmul(vec2d_swizzle2(A2, A2, 1), vec2d_swizzle2(DC2, DC1, 2)));
325 dC = vec2d_duplane(dC, 0);
326 iC1 = psub(a: pmul(a: B1, b: dC), b: iC1);
327 iC2 = psub(a: pmul(a: B2, b: dC), b: iC2);
328
329 const double sign_mask1[2] = {0.0, numext::bit_cast<double>(src: 0x8000000000000000ull)};
330 const double sign_mask2[2] = {numext::bit_cast<double>(src: 0x8000000000000000ull), 0.0};
331 const Packet2d sign_PN = ploadu<Packet2d>(from: sign_mask1);
332 const Packet2d sign_NP = ploadu<Packet2d>(from: sign_mask2);
333 d1 = pxor(a: rd, b: sign_PN);
334 d2 = pxor(a: rd, b: sign_NP);
335
336 Index res_stride = result.outerStride();
337 double *res = result.data();
338 pstoret<double, Packet2d, ResultAlignment>(res + 0, pmul(vec2d_swizzle2(iA2, iA1, 3), b: d1));
339 pstoret<double, Packet2d, ResultAlignment>(res + res_stride, pmul(vec2d_swizzle2(iA2, iA1, 0), b: d2));
340 pstoret<double, Packet2d, ResultAlignment>(res + 2, pmul(vec2d_swizzle2(iB2, iB1, 3), b: d1));
341 pstoret<double, Packet2d, ResultAlignment>(res + res_stride + 2, pmul(vec2d_swizzle2(iB2, iB1, 0), b: d2));
342 pstoret<double, Packet2d, ResultAlignment>(res + 2 * res_stride, pmul(vec2d_swizzle2(iC2, iC1, 3), b: d1));
343 pstoret<double, Packet2d, ResultAlignment>(res + 3 * res_stride, pmul(vec2d_swizzle2(iC2, iC1, 0), b: d2));
344 pstoret<double, Packet2d, ResultAlignment>(res + 2 * res_stride + 2, pmul(vec2d_swizzle2(iD2, iD1, 3), b: d1));
345 pstoret<double, Packet2d, ResultAlignment>(res + 3 * res_stride + 2, pmul(vec2d_swizzle2(iD2, iD1, 0), b: d2));
346 }
347};
348#endif
349} // namespace internal
350} // namespace Eigen
351#endif
